{"id":"2010.09058","submitter":"Pedro Frejlich","authors":"Lilian C. Brambila, Pedro Frejlich, David Mart\\'inez Torres","title":"Coregular submanifolds and Poisson submersions","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.SG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The purpose of this paper is to provide a framework to study Poisson\nstructures on the total space of fibrations with Poisson fibre and Poisson\nbase.\n  The literature on this topic has so far addressed mainly the case in which\nthe Poisson structure on fibres is locally trivial (Poisson fibre bundles and\ncoupling Poisson structures), or at the very least which admit a compatible\nEhresmann connection (almost-coupling Poisson structures).\n  However, important examples exist in nature -- for example, the ones in toric\ngeometry and Poisson-Lie groups we discuss in this note -- which behave as\ncouplings over leaves on the base, but which cannot admit compatible Ehresmann\nconnections.\n  This prompted us to study here general Poisson submersions whose fibres\ninherit Poisson structures. It turns out that the induced Poisson structure on\nfibres is always of an especially well-behaved nature -- what we call coregular\nsubmanifolds -- and that such Poisson submersions enjoy nice functorial\nproperties. This is a convenient setting to discuss the associated bundle\nconstruction absent even local triviality of the induced foliations, and we\napply our methods to produce Poisson structures with a finite number of leaves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 18 Oct 2020 18:36:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Aug 2022 17:46:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-30"}
