o both TKE and\n$\\langle u'_{x}u'_{r} \\rangle $. While $m=1$ captures the slope of the\nshear-stress profile near the centerline, $m=2$ is important to capture\n$\\langle u'_{x}u'_{r} \\rangle $ at and near its peak. SPOD is also performed in\nthe vicinity of the disk to describe the modal transition to the principal\ncontributors in the wake.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2020 07:56:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 20 Oct 2020 06:04:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-04"}
