ate low-momentum transfer region, leaving the sub-leading\nradiative chiral order effects to play a dominant role in this particular\nkinematic region. For the low-energy MUSE experiment, the often neglected\nlepton mass as well as the Pauli form factor contributions of the relativistic\nleptons are incorporated in all our computations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2020 11:08:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Jul 2021 20:51:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-15"}
